#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa → añña­bhāgi­ya­sikkhā­pada (kaṅkhāvitaraṇī)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:0.4"
msgid "Dutiya­duṭṭha­dosa­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "9. The second training rule on anger"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.167, pts-vp-en1.288, pts-cs-bu-ss9.1.1, ms1V_1626 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalanda­ka­nivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

# NOTE: See Suspension 8, [](MS.1.1565), for a comment on the present rendering of these names.
#. VAR: chagalakaṃ → chakalakaṃ (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena metti­ya­bhūma­jakā bhikkhū gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohantā addasaṃsu chagalakaṃ ajikāya vippa­ṭi­pajjan­taṃ."
msgstr "On one occasion the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka were descending from Mount Vulture Peak, when they saw two goats copulating."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.3"
msgid "Disvāna evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "They said to each other,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.4"
msgid "“handa mayaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ chagalakaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ nāma karoma."
msgstr "“Let’s give the he-goat the name Dabba the Mallian"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.5"
msgid "Imaṃ ajikaṃ mettiyaṃ nāma bhikkhuniṃ karoma."
msgstr "and the she-goat the name Mettiya the nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ voharissāma."
msgstr "We can then say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.7"
msgid "Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ sutena avocumhā."
msgstr "‘Earlier we spoke because of what we had heard about Dabba,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.8"
msgid "Idāni pana amhehi sāmaṃ diṭṭho mettiyāya bhikkhuniyā vippa­ṭi­pajjanto”ti."
msgstr "but now we’ve seen him ourselves copulating with the nun Mettiya.’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.9"
msgid "Te taṃ chagalakaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ nāma akaṃsu."
msgstr "They gave them those names"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.10"
msgid "Taṃ ajikaṃ mettiyaṃ nāma bhikkhuniṃ akaṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.11"
msgid "Te bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesuṃ—"
msgstr "and then told the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.12"
msgid "“pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ sutena avocumhā."
msgstr "“Earlier we spoke about what we had heard,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.13"
msgid "Idāni pana amhehi sāmaṃ diṭṭho mettiyāya bhikkhuniyā vippa­ṭi­pajjanto”ti."
msgstr "but now we’ve seen Dabba copulating with the nun Mettiya.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.14"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks replied,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.15"
msgid "“māvuso, evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Don’t say such a thing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.16"
msgid "Nāyasmā dabbo mallaputto evaṃ karissatī”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Dabba wouldn’t do that.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_1627 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.17"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.18"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master had the Order of monks assembled and asked Dabba,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.19"
msgid "“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathayime bhikkhū āhaṃsū”ti?"
msgstr "“Dabba, do you remember doing as these monks say?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.20"
msgid "“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, the Master knows about me.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.21"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "A second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.22"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and a third time the Master asked"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.23"
msgid "“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathayime bhikkhū āhaṃsū”ti?"
msgstr "the same question"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.24"
msgid "“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti."
msgstr "and got the same response."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.289
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.25"
msgid "“Na kho, dabba, dabbā evaṃ nibbeṭhenti."
msgstr "He then said, “Dabba, the Dabbas don’t give such evasive answers."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.26"
msgid "Sace tayā kataṃ katanti vadehi,"
msgstr "If it was done by you, say so;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.27"
msgid "sace tayā akataṃ akatanti vadehī”ti."
msgstr "if it wasn’t done by you, then say that.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.28"
msgid "“Yato ahaṃ, bhante, jāto nābhijānāmi supinantenapi methunadhammaṃ paṭisevitā, pageva jāgaro”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, since I was born I don’t recall having sexual intercourse even in a dream, much less when I was awake.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.29"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—“tena hi, bhikkhave, ime bhikkhū anuyuñjathā”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, monks, call those monks to account,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.1.30"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr "and he rose from his seat and entered his dwelling."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-cs-bu-ss9.1.2, ms1V_1628 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū metti­ya­bhūma­jake bhikkhū anuyuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "The monks then questioned Mettiya and Bhūmajaka, who told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.2"
msgid "Te bhikkhūhi anuyuñjīyamānā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.3"
msgid "“kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Did you accuse Venerable Dabba of an offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.4"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma metti­ya­bhūma­jakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃ­ses­santī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Mettiya and Bhūmajaka accuse Venerable Dabba like this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_1629 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.8"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū metti­ya­bhūma­jake bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They rebuked those monks in many ways and then told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsethā”ti?"
msgstr "He said, “Is it true, monks, that you accused Dabba the Mallian of an offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.12"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃ­ses­sa­tha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you accuse Dabba like this?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli3.168, ms1V_1630, pts-vp-en1.290
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ duṭṭho doso appatīto aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃseyya—"
msgstr "‘If a monk who is angry and displeased, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext, accuses another monk of an offense entailing expulsion,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.16"
msgid "‘appeva nāma naṃ imamhā brahmacariyā cāveyyan’ti."
msgstr "aiming to make him leave the monastic life,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:1.2.17"
msgid "Tato aparena samayena sama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā asama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā añña­bhāgi­yañ­ceva taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ hoti koci deso lesamatto upādinno, bhikkhu ca dosaṃ patiṭṭhāti, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "and then after some time, whether he is questioned or not, it is clear that the legal issue is unrelated and used as a pretext, and he admits to his ill-will, he commits an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-ss9.2.1, ms1V_1631
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_1632
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "Another monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "a different monk."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_1633
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.8"
msgid "Duṭṭho dosoti"
msgstr "Angry:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.9"
msgid "kupito anattamano anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "upset, dissatisfied, discontent, having hatred, hostile."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_1634
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.10"
msgid "Appatītoti"
msgstr "Displeased:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.1.11"
msgid "tena ca kopena, tena ca dosena, tāya ca anattamanatāya, tāya ca anabhiraddhiyā appatīto hoti."
msgstr "because of that upset, that ill-will, that dissatisfaction, and that discontent, he is displeased."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, pts-cs-bu-ss9.2.2, ms1V_1635
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.1"
msgid "Aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassāti"
msgstr "An unrelated legal issue:"

#. HTML: </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.2"
msgid "āpattañ­ña­bhāgi­yaṃ vā hoti adhika­ra­ṇañ­ña­bhāgi­yaṃ vā."
msgstr "It is either unrelated in regard to offenses or unrelated in regard to legal issues."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ?"
msgstr "How is a legal issue unrelated to a legal issue?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.4"
msgid "Vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa kic­cādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from a dispute is unrelated to a legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense, and a legal issue arising from a proceeding."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.5"
msgid "Anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa kic­cādhika­ra­ṇassa vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from an accusation is unrelated to a legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from a proceeding, and a legal issue arising from a dispute."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.6"
msgid "Āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ kic­cādhika­ra­ṇassa vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from an offense is unrelated to a legal issue arising from a proceeding, a legal issue arising from a dispute, and a legal issue arising from an accusation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.7"
msgid "Kic­cādhika­ra­ṇaṃ vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from a proceeding is unrelated to a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, and a legal issue arising from an offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "It is in this way that a legal issue is unrelated to a legal issue."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_1636 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.9"
msgid "Kathaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ?"
msgstr "How is a legal issue related to a legal issue?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.10"
msgid "Vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from a dispute is related to a legal issue arising from a dispute."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.11"
msgid "Anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from an accusation is related to a legal issue arising from an accusation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.12"
msgid "Āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa siyā tabbhāgiyaṃ siyā aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from an offense may be either related or unrelated to a legal issue arising from an offense."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_1637 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.13"
msgid "Kathaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ?"
msgstr "How is a legal issue arising from an offense unrelated to a legal issue arising from an offense?"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.291
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.14"
msgid "Methuna­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­patti adinnā­dāna­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā uttari­manus­sa­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā aññabhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to sexual intercourse is unrelated to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to stealing, an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a human being, and an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a superhuman quality."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.15"
msgid "Adinnā­dāna­pā­rāji­kā­patti manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā uttari­manus­sa­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā methuna­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā aññabhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to stealing is unrelated to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a human being, an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a superhuman quality, and an offense entailing expulsion in regard to sexual intercourse."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.16"
msgid "Manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kā­patti uttari­manus­sa­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā methuna­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā adinnā­dāna­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā aññabhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to a human being is unrelated to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a superhuman quality, an offense entailing expulsion in regard to sexual intercourse, and an offense entailing expulsion in regard to stealing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.17"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­patti methuna­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā adinnā­dāna­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā aññabhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to a superhuman quality is unrelated to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to sexual intercourse, an offense entailing expulsion in regard to stealing, and an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a human being."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.18"
msgid "Evaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "It is in this way that a legal issue arising from an offense is unrelated to a legal issue arising from an offense."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_1638 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.19"
msgid "Kathaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ?"
msgstr "How is a legal issue arising from an offense related to a legal issue arising from an offense?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.20"
msgid "Methuna­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­patti methuna­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā tabbhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to sexual intercourse is related to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to sexual intercourse."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.21"
msgid "Adinnā­dāna­pā­rāji­kā­patti adinnā­dāna­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā tabbhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to stealing is related to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to stealing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.22"
msgid "Manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kā­patti manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā tabbhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to a human being is related to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a human being."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.23"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­patti uttari­manus­sa­dhamma­pā­rāji­kā­pattiyā tabbhāgiyā."
msgstr "An offense entailing expulsion in regard to a superhuman quality is related to an offense entailing expulsion in regard to a superhuman quality."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.24"
msgid "Evaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "It is in this way that a legal issue arising from an offense is related to a legal issue arising from an offense."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_1639 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.25"
msgid "Kic­cādhika­ra­ṇaṃ kic­cādhika­ra­ṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "A legal issue arising from a proceeding is related to a legal issue arising from a proceeding."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:2.2.26"
msgid "Evaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "It is in this way that a legal issue is related to a legal issue."

